        "description": "In org/apache/hadoop/hdfs/server/datanode/DataXceiverServer.java, there is the following code snippet in the run() method:\n\n156:      } catch (OutOfMemoryError ie) {\n157:        IOUtils.cleanup(null, peer);\n158:        // DataNode can run out of memory if there is too many transfers.\n159:       // Log the event, Sleep for 30 seconds, other transfers may complete by\n160:        // then.\n161:        LOG.warn(\"DataNode is out of memory. Will retry in 30 seconds.\", ie);\n162:        try {\n163:          Thread.sleep(30 * 1000);\n164:        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\n165:          // ignore\n166:        }\n167:      }\n\nNote that InterruptedException is completely ignored. This might not be safe since any potential events that lead to InterruptedException are lost?\n\nMore info: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1087475/when-does-javas-thread-sleep-throw-interruptedexception\n\nThanks,\nDing",
